24:08.395 --> 24:09.777
We have already found religion.

24:10.117 --> 24:12.600
We already this, no soliciting.

24:13.562 --> 24:14.964
Which basically said, go away.

24:18.649 --> 24:19.570
Do we knock still?

24:20.194 --> 24:24.718
Do they really mean to push away the 12-year-old selling a candy bar?

24:25.920 --> 24:32.246
Or is it really more like the Kirby vacuum cleaner salesman guy or the Jehovah's Witnesses that like to walk the neighborhood?

24:34.908 --> 24:38.752
Let's see, we allow ourselves to be afraid of the rejection that might be there.

24:38.772 --> 24:40.313
So what does a 12-year-old boy do?

24:40.854 --> 24:43.517
He goes, I'm not knocking on that door and go to the next one.

24:44.197 --> 24:49.202
When they very well might have liked to have a caramel whatever candy bar.

24:52.482 --> 24:59.049
The other thing that plays into this fear of rejection is that we may have experienced rejection in the past.

25:01.231 --> 25:06.537
And the idea of opening ourselves up again, frankly, is just too painful.

25:08.799 --> 25:13.865
We've had somebody push us away, somebody we cared about deeply.

25:13.885 --> 25:16.748
And it doesn't even have to be about a witnessing thing.

25:16.768 --> 25:18.610
It can be rejection for anything.

25:19.426 --> 25:27.518
A boyfriend, a girlfriend that you just were absolutely in love with, and all of a sudden, they're with a different boy or girl.

25:30.022 --> 25:33.567
Somebody that you care deeply about and relationship went bad.

25:37.193 --> 25:41.059
So rather than risk the rejection, we remain silent.

25:43.002 --> 25:45.906
We simply, again, we put ourselves in our bubble.

25:48.738 --> 25:52.703
because we want to avoid the risk altogether.

25:55.647 --> 26:03.517
But see, Scripture assures us that if God is for us, no one can truly be against us.

26:03.678 --> 26:09.666
Romans 8 chapter 8 and verse 31, what shall we say about such wonderful things as these?

26:10.026 --> 26:15.133
If God is for us, who can ever be against us?

26:15.553 --> 26:16.114
Amen?

26:17.826 --> 26:21.029
Again, this doesn't mean that we're not gonna face rejection, we will.

26:24.212 --> 26:26.094
It just means that we don't need to fear it.

26:27.896 --> 26:34.742
Rejection happens, it's gonna happen to everybody and it's, whether you try to insulate yourself or not, it's going to happen.

26:35.082 --> 26:47.314
You're gonna be passed over for a promotion, you're gonna be passed over for a romantic relationship, you're gonna be passed over for some thing that you really wanted, whatever it may be, it's gonna happen.

26:49.794 --> 26:51.316
But here's the amazing thing.

26:51.996 --> 26:54.379
We have to put things in context.

26:55.380 --> 27:00.025
We are really good at isolating individual parts of our lives.

27:00.686 --> 27:02.909
Men, we do this more than the ladies do.

27:04.070 --> 27:05.732
We are compartmental thinkers.

27:09.356 --> 27:10.917
But can I make a connection for you?

27:13.480 --> 27:15.162
Rejection's gonna happen.

27:17.024 --> 27:18.706
But God has already accepted us.

27:20.130 --> 27:22.033
Acceptance has already happened.

27:22.353 --> 27:26.099
And that is the only approval that we really need.

27:28.903 --> 27:30.706
Oh, that one should have got at least an amen or two.

27:32.488 --> 27:33.971
His approval is all that we need.

27:34.171 --> 27:35.092
I know we're human.

27:35.513 --> 27:38.798
I know we desperately seek human connection.

27:38.838 --> 27:39.939
We were made for that.

27:41.141 --> 27:47.090
But at the end of the day, the only thing that we need, the only acceptance that we need is his.

27:48.290 --> 27:50.192
Think about the apostles in the early church.

27:50.232 --> 27:55.880
They faced rejection time and time again as they went out and tried to spread the gospel.

27:56.120 --> 28:00.305
People laughed at them, they ignored them, and sometimes they violently rejected them.

28:01.126 --> 28:08.676
But they continued to preach what they knew that God had for them because they knew that God was with them.

28:09.056 --> 28:13.842
And in the same way we can take comfort in knowing that even if

28:14.082 --> 28:18.708
A neighbor doesn't respond the way that we really would like, the way that we would hope.

28:20.190 --> 28:24.255
God sees our effort and he walks with us every step of the way.

28:26.038 --> 28:33.187
Remember, some plant, some water, God gives the increase.

28:34.229 --> 28:38.534
In evangelism, increase is not on your shoulders.

28:40.016 --> 28:41.298
That is God's part.

28:42.242 --> 28:55.941
Your job is to overcome fear, speak the truth in love, and allow the seed that gets planted to be watered, and then ultimately for God to blossom it.

28:55.961 --> 29:04.953
Sometimes he does that right there in the one setting, and you plant the seed, you water the seed, you tend to the soil by answering the questions all right there.

29:05.413 --> 29:07.276
And then God says, I'm ready.

29:09.118 --> 29:11.762
Hey, would you like to pray and accept Jesus today?

29:12.674 --> 29:13.215
Yes, I would.

29:14.416 --> 29:21.346
But sometimes, say, I just want you to know that as a Christian, I'm going to be praying for you.

29:21.446 --> 29:27.794
I know you're not a believer, but my God can answer all of your desires and all of your needs.

29:29.176 --> 29:29.777
So I'm ready.

29:29.917 --> 29:31.900
I'm willing and I'm going to pray for you this week.

29:31.940 --> 29:33.442
And so now the seed has been planted.

29:33.802 --> 29:39.730
And then somebody else comes along and says, Hey, I heard that you're going through something.

29:41.794 --> 29:44.838
And I know they're praying for you, but can I?

29:46.921 --> 29:49.625
And then somewhere down the line, God does the increase.

29:55.333 --> 30:01.241
Fear is a natural response, but it's not from God.

30:02.824 --> 30:08.151
It's built into who we are as human beings, but what is our original passage?

30:08.832 --> 30:10.194
Tell us that we have?

30:11.586 --> 30:16.555
says that God gives us a spirit of power, love, and sound judgment.

30:17.957 --> 30:24.068
When we feel fear rising up within us, we need to remind ourselves of that truth.

30:26.052 --> 30:34.226
We have to stop letting fear of the unknown or fear of rejection dictate how we interact with those around us.

30:35.906 --> 30:46.980
We need to begin to ask God for the courage to take the first step and trusting that He is with us and that His love will overcome any fear that we might have.

30:51.306 --> 31:03.922
Second thing we need to look at when we talk about building courageous connections, overcoming the fear factor, is we need to look at the impact of fear on our relationships.

31:05.922 --> 31:09.246
See, fear doesn't just stop us from engaging with others.

31:09.506 --> 31:15.693
It distorts how we see people around us and the relationships that God calls us to build.

31:18.957 --> 31:21.119
When we leave, it unchecked.

31:21.700 --> 31:34.354
Fear can make us view our neighbors not as fellow humans that are created in God's image, but our fight or flight instincts can kick in.

31:35.682 --> 31:49.119
And all of the sudden, we might see the other people that God is calling us to as the enemy, as something to be feared, as something that might be a potential threat or an obstacle or an inconvenience.

31:50.241 --> 31:55.928
But look at what first John chapter four in verse 18 says.

31:55.968 --> 32:03.858
Where's my passage at?

32:04.770 --> 32:05.832
Did I not get it in there?

32:05.852 --> 32:07.935
I didn't get it in there, so I'm just gonna read it to you.

32:12.482 --> 32:17.330
It says this, such love has no fear because perfect love expels all fear.

32:18.111 --> 32:28.368
If we are afraid, it is for fear of punishment, and this is how this shows that we have not fully experienced his perfect love.

32:28.648 --> 32:29.810
Let me read that again.

32:30.690 --> 32:39.525
Such love, this is 1 John 4 18, such love has no fear because perfect love expels all fear.

32:40.627 --> 32:44.554
If we're afraid, it is for fear of punishment.

32:45.396 --> 32:49.423
And this shows that we have not fully experienced his perfect love.

32:52.749 --> 32:55.794
See, fear distorts our view of others.

32:57.506 --> 33:00.511
Fear changes how we perceive the world around us.

33:00.591 --> 33:03.837
It magnifies the negative and it diminishes the positive.

33:04.377 --> 33:12.471
In Scripture, we see how clearly the story of the Israelites spies who were sent out to explore the promised land.

33:14.274 --> 33:21.586
Numbers chapter 13 and verse 33, 10 of the 12 spies that went out came back.

33:21.730 --> 33:26.418
and they brought back the story of what was going on in the promised land.

33:26.758 --> 33:30.725
Ten of them came back filled with fear, and this is what they said.

33:30.765 --> 33:36.614
It says, we even saw giants there, the descendants of an ox.

33:37.556 --> 33:43.826
Next to them, we felt like grasshoppers, and that's what they thought too.

33:46.338 --> 33:55.428
Their fear caused them to see themselves as weak and small, and it distorted their perception of the inhabitants of the land.

33:57.311 --> 34:07.442
The truth is that God had already promised them the victory, but their fear blinded them to the reality of what God had done.

34:10.806 --> 34:14.130
When we talk about this in context of our modern day,

34:16.354 --> 34:18.857
This is much like the way that we see our neighbors.

34:21.099 --> 34:23.522
We think, ah, they'll never be interested in talking to me.

34:23.562 --> 34:24.823
They're too different from me.

34:25.124 --> 34:26.986
We won't have anything in common.

34:29.769 --> 34:37.397
And these beliefs, these fears are often based on assumptions rather than on the truth.

34:40.000 --> 34:42.423
The big burly biker guy I always talk about.

34:44.545 --> 34:45.586
Can I tell you the truth?

34:45.986 --> 34:47.288
He's really not all that big.

34:48.169 --> 34:49.631
He's really not all that burly.

34:50.472 --> 34:52.195
He's really not all that inked up.

34:54.358 --> 34:58.644
But because we're afraid, it seems more than it is.

35:01.007 --> 35:03.451
This applies in many areas of our lives.

35:05.073 --> 35:14.066
When we're afraid of what somebody is doing, all of the sudden, the couple of things that they're doing, that because we're afraid,

35:14.754 --> 35:20.004
It seems huge, and the old phrase is we make mountains out of mole hills.

35:21.326 --> 35:30.444
Something that's really rather insignificant is this huge issue, and we have to be careful that we don't allow that.

35:31.025 --> 35:31.305
Why?

35:31.345 --> 35:33.810
Because fear leads to isolation.

35:35.778 --> 35:41.104
Fear not only distorts our view of others, but it causes us to retreat into isolation.

35:41.325 --> 35:50.015
When we allow fear to control us, we avoid meaningful interactions with people around us, leaving us disconnected and alone.

35:53.359 --> 35:55.341
This is the opposite of what God calls us to.

35:55.922 --> 35:56.622
Why do we know that?

35:56.662 --> 35:58.925
Look at Proverbs chapter 18 and verse one.

35:59.826 --> 36:03.090
Says, whoever isolates himself seeks his own desire.

36:03.714 --> 36:06.317
He breaks out against all sound judgment.

36:08.640 --> 36:26.341
If you're pulling away from the community, if you're pulling away from your neighbor, if you're pulling away from the group, we'll say here at church, then there's a good chance that there's a bit of selfishness built in.

36:28.984 --> 36:30.546
And we need to check our own hearts.

36:34.498 --> 36:39.686
because the isolation can be a form of self-protection, but it's not God's design for us.

36:39.706 --> 36:46.197
1 John 4 18 again reminds us that perfect love drives out fear.

36:48.300 --> 36:54.691
Love pulls us out of the isolation and pushes us towards these meaningful connections.

36:55.131 --> 36:57.836
Fear builds walls, but love builds bridges.

36:58.397 --> 36:59.158
That's tweetable.

37:00.741 --> 37:01.682
That's a note taker.

37:03.906 --> 37:07.893
Fear builds walls, but love builds bridges.

37:09.896 --> 37:14.964
When we allow God's love to flow through us, it drives away the fear that keeps us disconnected.

37:17.448 --> 37:26.223
The third thing that we need to look at when we talk about overcoming the fear factors, breaking through, breaking through this fear factor.

37:28.226 --> 37:30.770
Look at what Joshua chapter one in verse nine says,

37:31.074 --> 37:32.501
Says, this is my command.

37:32.863 --> 37:35.195
Be weak and afraid.

37:35.236 --> 37:38.834
No, no, that's not what that says, does it?

37:40.546 --> 37:43.409
Says, this is my command, be strong and courageous.

37:43.830 --> 37:50.557
Don't be afraid or discouraged for the Lord your God is with you wherever you go.

37:50.977 --> 37:54.261
That means across the street or next door to your neighbors.

37:54.621 --> 37:58.606
That means when you reach across the cubicle wall and talk to somebody.

37:58.806 --> 38:01.429
That means that he is there here in church.

38:02.270 --> 38:02.510
Why?

38:02.590 --> 38:06.955
Because he calls us to step out in faith and courage.

38:06.975 --> 38:10.098
His presence overcomes fear.

38:14.946 --> 38:20.731
The command that God gave Joshua is as relevant for us today as it was then.

38:21.012 --> 38:23.794
He didn't promise Joshua that everything would be easy.

38:23.834 --> 38:29.680
He said, don't be afraid because I'll be with you wherever you go.

38:29.720 --> 38:32.583
Don't be afraid.

38:33.123 --> 38:34.725
Not because it's gonna be easy.

38:34.765 --> 38:36.967
Not because there won't be giants in the land.

38:37.287 --> 38:41.131
Not because I'm gonna make a path so you can walk on through.

38:41.451 --> 38:44.754
He says, when you go, I'm with you.

38:46.402 --> 38:49.145
One passage says, when you walk through the fire, I will be there.

38:50.687 --> 38:51.768
You will not be burned.

38:55.513 --> 38:57.034
Think about the three Hebrew children.

39:00.699 --> 39:02.541
You gotta figure that they were terrified.

39:03.302 --> 39:04.263
They're still human.

39:04.683 --> 39:08.027
Yes, they had faith, faith-like giants.

39:11.491 --> 39:13.714
But there was still a furnace

39:14.882 --> 39:18.687
And they knew, I mean, we know what fire does to the human body, yeah?

39:22.213 --> 39:23.354
And they're about to be thrown in.

39:26.358 --> 39:26.819
Okay, God.

39:32.607 --> 39:36.653
God, you've called me to worship you, and this is where it's ended me up in my life.

39:38.376 --> 39:39.958
So in a moment, I'm gonna meet you.

39:41.620 --> 39:42.802
And my life is over.

39:43.938 --> 39:48.584
But may I stand before you found innocent?

39:54.311 --> 39:54.731
In they go.

39:57.555 --> 39:58.336
They're standing there.

40:01.319 --> 40:02.701
All of a sudden nothing's happening.

40:05.525 --> 40:09.970
I can't imagine that it wasn't hot, but they weren't being burned.

40:11.906 --> 40:16.931
And then all of a sudden, there was somebody else standing in the fire with them.

40:16.951 --> 40:22.678
And my God says, don't be afraid because I am there with you.

40:25.320 --> 40:37.874
When we walk across the street, when we knock on our neighbor's door, last time I checked, they didn't have a flamethrower sitting at their front door.

40:39.586 --> 40:44.912
So anything less than that, would you call good?

40:46.173 --> 40:52.420
Because they're not lighting you up on fire, but yet he still says, I'm there with you.

40:54.803 --> 40:55.644
Don't be afraid.

41:02.051 --> 41:08.178
He calls us to step out and to make disciples

41:08.802 --> 41:11.185
I referenced this earlier, Matthew 28, 20.

41:17.912 --> 41:22.778
Teach these new disciples to obey all the commands that I've given you and be sure of this.

41:24.560 --> 41:29.045
I am with you always even to the end of the age.

41:31.167 --> 41:31.567
Guess what?

41:32.949 --> 41:37.394
We're at the end of the age and he's still here and he's still with us.

41:40.994 --> 41:44.539
because at the end of the day, love is the antidote to fear.

41:47.783 --> 41:50.667
I don't know what's going on in your life and I don't know what's happening.

41:55.353 --> 42:00.801
I learned a long time ago that anger is just fear turned outward.

42:01.502 --> 42:02.403
I'm sorry, it turned outward.

42:05.928 --> 42:07.730
Anger is just fear.

42:10.786 --> 42:13.792
If you're angry, you're fearful.

42:16.357 --> 42:19.063
If you're doubting, you're fearful.

42:22.530 --> 42:28.722
So can I tell you, love is the antidote to that fear.

42:31.586 --> 42:40.640
Now, if you remember other lessons we have learned and you have learned, I am 100% positive that you have heard from other pastors.

42:42.703 --> 42:44.306
Love is not a feeling.

42:45.608 --> 42:46.329
Love is a choice.

42:48.853 --> 42:59.570
So if love is a choice and love is the antidote to fear, if I am angry or if I am battling doubt, then I can choose to love

42:59.874 --> 43:09.027
An action, I can make an action, I can do something to overcome the fear, the anger, the doubt.

43:10.088 --> 43:15.856
Even if I don't feel like it, husbands and wives, this is applicable to you.

43:16.517 --> 43:24.348
We very often, in counseling as a pastor, I will talk to people and they're just like, I just don't feel in love anymore.

43:24.688 --> 43:28.914
The spark isn't there like it was when we first got married.

43:29.922 --> 43:35.649
And you don't look the way you did when we first got married.

43:35.689 --> 43:39.073
Amen.

43:42.558 --> 43:43.639
But love is a choice.

43:43.659 --> 43:49.026
I choose to wake up every morning and I choose to love my wife.

43:49.927 --> 43:51.228
I don't always feel like it.

43:51.389 --> 43:52.690
Don't aim in from over there.

43:54.973 --> 43:59.058
I don't always feel like it, but I choose to love my wife.

43:59.618 --> 44:04.124
I choose to work through the challenges that we have in our marriage.

44:04.465 --> 44:06.488
I choose to love my children.

44:06.868 --> 44:15.701
I choose daily to wake up and pray over every one of you and to love every one of you as the shepherd, as the pastor of the church.

44:17.703 --> 44:24.293
Whether you like me or not, I choose to love you.

44:24.313 --> 44:28.018
And we need to choose to love our neighbor as ourself.

44:29.282 --> 44:31.365
Because this is what God has called us to do.

44:43.424 --> 44:44.065
So is that close?

44:47.270 --> 44:50.635
We need to take a moment and reflect on some of these ideas that we've come to.

44:52.318 --> 44:57.746
Because fear is something that we all deal with, whether it's the fear of the unknown, fear of rejection,

44:57.858 --> 45:02.323
or the fear that keeps us from fully engaging with the people around us.

45:04.365 --> 45:06.748
Remember, fear distorts our perception.

45:07.048 --> 45:14.276
It isolates us from others, and it prevents us from living out the command to love our neighbor as ourselves.

45:15.777 --> 45:20.562
But the good news is this, and we start where we finish where we started.

45:20.903 --> 45:27.570
For God has not given us a spirit of fear and timidity, but of power and of love and of self-discipline.

45:31.234 --> 45:46.173
Through His presence, we have the courage to step out in faith and to build relationships that reflect Him, not me, Him, and to overcome fear that holds us back.

45:49.858 --> 45:52.682
Remember, fear is not from God.

45:55.205 --> 45:59.250
It often stems from our fear of the unknown or fear of rejection.

46:02.370 --> 46:17.831
Fear distorts how we view others, can cause us to self-isolate, but God gives us perfect love to cast out fear, and it enables us to build healthy, life-giving relationships.

46:20.474 --> 46:24.700
And with God's presence and love, we can step out in faith.

46:24.720 --> 46:26.162
We can overcome our fears,

46:26.466 --> 46:32.512
We can engage in meaningful relationship, meaningful connections with our neighbors.

46:35.035 --> 46:36.637
How do we grow Berea Temple?

46:38.699 --> 46:49.891
By stepping out in faith and building courageously, building connections with those around us.

46:52.393 --> 46:53.234
So let's pray.

46:56.098 --> 46:58.441
Father, You've called us to step out.

46:59.523 --> 47:04.530
For some of us, it's stepping out into the fire because we are not good at conversation.

47:05.631 --> 47:09.897
We are not good at stepping out in faith and talking to our neighbors.

47:13.702 --> 47:22.034
For some of us, Lord, the fear just grips us too much.

47:24.066 --> 47:25.848
So we don't know the name of our neighbors.

47:25.868 --> 47:27.310
We don't know who lives around us.

47:27.370 --> 47:31.014
We don't know anything about them.

47:31.034 --> 47:36.681
But we do know that you're calling us to step out and build courageous connections.

47:40.325 --> 47:42.928
So with every head bowed and every eye closed, nobody's looking around.

47:42.948 --> 47:49.175
I want to offer two invitations as I typically do.

47:49.195 --> 47:51.698
First is for those who have been living with fear,

47:52.162 --> 47:58.749
whether it's fear of reaching out to others, fear of rejection, or fear of stepping out of your comfort zone.

47:58.769 --> 48:01.191
I want to invite you to bring those fears to God.

48:03.654 --> 48:10.220
Ask Him for the courage to step out in faith and to trust that His presence will guide and go with you.

48:11.802 --> 48:16.967
The second invitation is for anyone who has never experienced the love of Christ.

48:17.688 --> 48:19.890
The love that drives out all fear.

48:20.642 --> 48:23.165
I want to invite you today to receive that love.

48:24.507 --> 48:37.162
Jesus overcame the greatest fear that is death itself so that we might have life and have it abundantly.

48:37.182 --> 48:47.314
And so if you're ready to invite Christ into your life, we'll call you to step out of the fear today and come forward or reach out to us online.

48:50.562 --> 48:55.349
commitment today.

48:55.369 --> 49:00.617
So as our worship team plays, the altar is open.

49:03.381 --> 49:07.167
You are more than welcome if you need time in the presence of the Lord.

49:07.407 --> 49:11.434
If you need to respond, we invite you during the singing to come and to respond.

49:11.454 --> 49:12.635
Somebody would love to pray with you.

49:12.916 --> 49:17.042
But if you just need time to pray, you need time alone.

49:17.186 --> 49:17.887
with the Lord.

49:18.188 --> 49:19.329
The altars are open.

49:19.409 --> 49:22.153
Our altars are these benches that are down front.

49:22.254 --> 49:28.323
They are altars or of course you can come and sit at the steps as well.

49:29.745 --> 49:33.450
However you want to pray, maybe you simply want to sit in your seat.

49:35.073 --> 49:36.535
Take the next couple of moments.

49:40.241 --> 49:43.826
Speak to the Lord and give those fears up.

